60 static int
61 __kmp_match_with_sentinel( char const * a, char const * b, size_t len, char sentinel ) {
62  size_t l = 0;
63 
64  if(a == NULL)
65  a = "";
66  if(b == NULL)
67  b = "";
68  while(*a && *b && *b != sentinel) {
69  char ca = *a, cb = *b;
70 
71  if(ca >= 'a' && ca <= 'z')
72  ca -= 'a' - 'A';
73  if(cb >= 'a' && cb <= 'z')
74  cb -= 'a' - 'A';
75  if(ca != cb)
76  return FALSE;
77  ++l;
78  ++a;
79  ++b;
80  }
81  return l >= len;
82 }

84 //
85 // Expected usage:
86 // token is the token to check for.
87 // buf is the string being parsed.
88 // *end returns the char after the end of the token.
89 // it is not modified unless a match occurs.
90 //
91 //
92 // Example 1:
93 //
94 // if (__kmp_match_str("token", buf, *end) {
95 // <do something>
96 // buf = end;
97 // }
98 //
99 // Example 2:
100 //
101 // if (__kmp_match_str("token", buf, *end) {
102 // char *save = **end;
103 // **end = sentinel;
104 // <use any of the __kmp*_with_sentinel() functions>
105 // **end = save;
106 // buf = end;
107 // }
108 //
109 
110 static int
111 __kmp_match_str( char const *token, char const *buf, const char **end) {
112 
113  KMP_ASSERT(token != NULL);
114  KMP_ASSERT(buf != NULL);
115  KMP_ASSERT(end != NULL);
116 
117  while (*token && *buf) {
118  char ct = *token, cb = *buf;
119 
120  if(ct >= 'a' && ct <= 'z')
121  ct -= 'a' - 'A';
122  if(cb >= 'a' && cb <= 'z')
123  cb -= 'a' - 'A';
124  if (ct != cb)
125  return FALSE;
126  ++token;
127  ++buf;
128  }
129  if (*token) {
130  return FALSE;
131  }
132  *end = buf;
133  return TRUE;
134 }

137 static size_t
138 __kmp_round4k( size_t size ) {
139  size_t _4k = 4 * 1024;
140  if ( size & ( _4k - 1 ) ) {
141  size &= ~ ( _4k - 1 );
142  if ( size <= KMP_SIZE_T_MAX - _4k ) {
143  size += _4k; // Round up if there is no overflow.
144  }; // if
145  }; // if
146  return size;
147 } // __kmp_round4k

150 /*
151  Here, multipliers are like __kmp_convert_to_seconds, but floating-point
152  values are allowed, and the return value is in milliseconds. The default
153  multiplier is milliseconds. Returns INT_MAX only if the value specified
154  matches "infinit*". Returns -1 if specified string is invalid.
155 */
156 int
157 __kmp_convert_to_milliseconds( char const * data )
158 {
159  int ret, nvalues, factor;
160  char mult, extra;
161  double value;
162 
163  if (data == NULL) return (-1);
164  if ( __kmp_str_match( "infinit", -1, data)) return (INT_MAX);
165  value = (double) 0.0;
166  mult = '\0';
167  nvalues = KMP_SSCANF (data, "%lf%c%c", &value, &mult, &extra);
168  if (nvalues < 1) return (-1);
169  if (nvalues == 1) mult = '\0';
170  if (nvalues == 3) return (-1);
171 
172  if (value < 0) return (-1);
173 
174  switch (mult) {
175  case '\0':
176  /* default is milliseconds */
177  factor = 1;
178  break;
179  case 's': case 'S':
180  factor = 1000;
181  break;
182  case 'm': case 'M':
183  factor = 1000 * 60;
184  break;
185  case 'h': case 'H':
186  factor = 1000 * 60 * 60;
187  break;
188  case 'd': case 'D':
189  factor = 1000 * 24 * 60 * 60;
190  break;
191  default:
192  return (-1);
193  }
194 
195  if ( value >= ( (INT_MAX-1) / factor) )
196  ret = INT_MAX-1; /* Don't allow infinite value here */
197  else
198  ret = (int) (value * (double) factor); /* truncate to int */
199 
200  return ret;
201 }

204 static int
205 __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( char const * a, char const * b, char sentinel ) {
206  if(a == NULL)
207  a = "";
208  if(b == NULL)
209  b = "";
210  while(*a && *b && *b != sentinel) {
211  char ca = *a, cb = *b;
212 
213  if(ca >= 'a' && ca <= 'z')
214  ca -= 'a' - 'A';
215  if(cb >= 'a' && cb <= 'z')
216  cb -= 'a' - 'A';
217  if(ca != cb)
218  return (int)(unsigned char)*a - (int)(unsigned char)*b;
219  ++a;
220  ++b;
221  }
222  return *a ?
223  (*b && *b != sentinel) ? (int)(unsigned char)*a - (int)(unsigned char)*b : 1 :
224  (*b && *b != sentinel) ? -1 : 0;
225 }

297 static void
298 __kmp_stg_parse_size(
299  char const * name,
300  char const * value,
301  size_t size_min,
302  size_t size_max,
303  int * is_specified,
304  size_t * out,
305  size_t factor
306 ) {
307  char const * msg = NULL;
308  #if KMP_OS_DARWIN
309  size_min = __kmp_round4k( size_min );
310  size_max = __kmp_round4k( size_max );
311  #endif // KMP_OS_DARWIN
312  if ( value ) {
313  if ( is_specified != NULL ) {
314  * is_specified = 1;
315  }; // if
316  __kmp_str_to_size( value, out, factor, & msg );
317  if ( msg == NULL ) {
318  if ( * out > size_max ) {
319  * out = size_max;
320  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooLarge );
321  } else if ( * out < size_min ) {
322  * out = size_min;
323  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooSmall );
324  } else {
325  #if KMP_OS_DARWIN
326  size_t round4k = __kmp_round4k( * out );
327  if ( * out != round4k ) {
328  * out = round4k;
329  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( NotMultiple4K );
330  }; // if
331  #endif
332  }; // if
333  } else {
334  // If integer overflow occurred, * out == KMP_SIZE_T_MAX. Cut it to size_max silently.
335  if ( * out < size_min ) {
336  * out = size_max;
337  }
338  else if ( * out > size_max ) {
339  * out = size_max;
340  }; // if
341  }; // if
342  if ( msg != NULL ) {
343  // Message is not empty. Print warning.
344  kmp_str_buf_t buf;
345  __kmp_str_buf_init( & buf );
346  __kmp_str_buf_print_size( & buf, * out );
347  KMP_WARNING( ParseSizeIntWarn, name, value, msg );
348  KMP_INFORM( Using_str_Value, name, buf.str );
349  __kmp_str_buf_free( & buf );
350  }; // if
351  }; // if
352 } // __kmp_stg_parse_size

366 static void
367 __kmp_stg_parse_int(
368  char const * name, // I: Name of environment variable (used in warning messages).
369  char const * value, // I: Value of environment variable to parse.
370  int min, // I: Miminal allowed value.
371  int max, // I: Maximum allowed value.
372  int * out // O: Output (parsed) value.
373 ) {
374  char const * msg = NULL;
375  kmp_uint64 uint = * out;
376  __kmp_str_to_uint( value, & uint, & msg );
377  if ( msg == NULL ) {
378  if ( uint < (unsigned int)min ) {
379  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooSmall );
380  uint = min;
381  } else if ( uint > (unsigned int)max ) {
382  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooLarge );
383  uint = max;
384  }; // if
385  } else {
386  // If overflow occurred msg contains error message and uint is very big. Cut tmp it
387  // to INT_MAX.
388  if ( uint < (unsigned int)min ) {
389  uint = min;
390  }
391  else if ( uint > (unsigned int)max ) {
392  uint = max;
393  }; // if
394  }; // if
395  if ( msg != NULL ) {
396  // Message is not empty. Print warning.
397  kmp_str_buf_t buf;
398  KMP_WARNING( ParseSizeIntWarn, name, value, msg );
399  __kmp_str_buf_init( & buf );
400  __kmp_str_buf_print( &buf, "%" KMP_UINT64_SPEC "", uint );
401  KMP_INFORM( Using_uint64_Value, name, buf.str );
402  __kmp_str_buf_free( &buf );
403  }; // if
404  * out = uint;
405 } // __kmp_stg_parse_int

432 static void
433 __kmp_stg_parse_par_range(
434  char const * name,
435  char const * value,
436  int * out_range,
437  char * out_routine,
438  char * out_file,
439  int * out_lb,
440  int * out_ub
441 ) {
442  size_t len = KMP_STRLEN( value + 1 );
443  par_range_to_print = (char *) KMP_INTERNAL_MALLOC( len +1 );
444  KMP_STRNCPY_S( par_range_to_print, len + 1, value, len + 1);
445  __kmp_par_range = +1;
446  __kmp_par_range_lb = 0;
447  __kmp_par_range_ub = INT_MAX;
448  for (;;) {
449  unsigned int len;
450  if (( value == NULL ) || ( *value == '\0' )) {
451  break;
452  }
453  if ( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "routine", value, '=' )) {
454  value = strchr( value, '=' ) + 1;
455  len = __kmp_readstr_with_sentinel( out_routine,
456  value, KMP_PAR_RANGE_ROUTINE_LEN - 1, ',' );
457  if ( len == 0 ) {
458  goto par_range_error;
459  }
460  value = strchr( value, ',' );
461  if ( value != NULL ) {
462  value++;
463  }
464  continue;
465  }
466  if ( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "filename", value, '=' )) {
467  value = strchr( value, '=' ) + 1;
468  len = __kmp_readstr_with_sentinel( out_file,
469  value, KMP_PAR_RANGE_FILENAME_LEN - 1, ',' );
470  if ( len == 0) {
471  goto par_range_error;
472  }
473  value = strchr( value, ',' );
474  if ( value != NULL ) {
475  value++;
476  }
477  continue;
478  }
479  if (( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "range", value, '=' ))
480  || ( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "incl_range", value, '=' ))) {
481  value = strchr( value, '=' ) + 1;
482  if ( KMP_SSCANF( value, "%d:%d", out_lb, out_ub ) != 2 ) {
483  goto par_range_error;
484  }
485  *out_range = +1;
486  value = strchr( value, ',' );
487  if ( value != NULL ) {
488  value++;
489  }
490  continue;
491  }
492  if ( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "excl_range", value, '=' )) {
493  value = strchr( value, '=' ) + 1;
494  if ( KMP_SSCANF( value, "%d:%d", out_lb, out_ub) != 2 ) {
495  goto par_range_error;
496  }
497  *out_range = -1;
498  value = strchr( value, ',' );
499  if ( value != NULL ) {
500  value++;
501  }
502  continue;
503  }
504  par_range_error:
505  KMP_WARNING( ParRangeSyntax, name );
506  __kmp_par_range = 0;
507  break;
508  }
509 } // __kmp_stg_parse_par_range
510 #endif

512 int
513 __kmp_initial_threads_capacity( int req_nproc )
514 {
515  int nth = 32;
516 
517  /* MIN( MAX( 32, 4 * $OMP_NUM_THREADS, 4 * omp_get_num_procs() ), __kmp_max_nth) */
518  if (nth < (4 * req_nproc))
519  nth = (4 * req_nproc);
520  if (nth < (4 * __kmp_xproc))
521  nth = (4 * __kmp_xproc);
522 
523  if (nth > __kmp_max_nth)
524  nth = __kmp_max_nth;
525 
526  return nth;
527 }

641 static void
642 __kmp_stg_parse_blocktime( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
643  __kmp_dflt_blocktime = __kmp_convert_to_milliseconds( value );
644  if ( __kmp_dflt_blocktime < 0 ) {
645  __kmp_dflt_blocktime = KMP_DEFAULT_BLOCKTIME;
646  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( InvalidValue, name, value ), __kmp_msg_null );
647  KMP_INFORM( Using_int_Value, name, __kmp_dflt_blocktime );
648  __kmp_env_blocktime = FALSE; // Revert to default as if var not set.
649  } else {
650  if ( __kmp_dflt_blocktime < KMP_MIN_BLOCKTIME ) {
651  __kmp_dflt_blocktime = KMP_MIN_BLOCKTIME;
652  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( SmallValue, name, value ), __kmp_msg_null );
653  KMP_INFORM( MinValueUsing, name, __kmp_dflt_blocktime );
654  } else if ( __kmp_dflt_blocktime > KMP_MAX_BLOCKTIME ) {
655  __kmp_dflt_blocktime = KMP_MAX_BLOCKTIME;
656  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( LargeValue, name, value ), __kmp_msg_null );
657  KMP_INFORM( MaxValueUsing, name, __kmp_dflt_blocktime );
658  }; // if
659  __kmp_env_blocktime = TRUE; // KMP_BLOCKTIME was specified.
660  }; // if
661  // calculate number of monitor thread wakeup intervals corresonding to blocktime.
662  __kmp_monitor_wakeups = KMP_WAKEUPS_FROM_BLOCKTIME( __kmp_dflt_blocktime, __kmp_monitor_wakeups );
663  __kmp_bt_intervals = KMP_INTERVALS_FROM_BLOCKTIME( __kmp_dflt_blocktime, __kmp_monitor_wakeups );
664  K_DIAG( 1, ( "__kmp_env_blocktime == %d\n", __kmp_env_blocktime ) );
665  if ( __kmp_env_blocktime ) {
666  K_DIAG( 1, ( "__kmp_dflt_blocktime == %d\n", __kmp_dflt_blocktime ) );
667  }
668 } // __kmp_stg_parse_blocktime

714 
715 static void
716 __kmp_stg_parse_wait_policy( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
717 
718  kmp_stg_wp_data_t * wait = (kmp_stg_wp_data_t *) data;
719  int rc;
720 
721  rc = __kmp_stg_check_rivals( name, value, wait->rivals );
722  if ( rc ) {
723  return;
724  }; // if
725 
726  if ( wait->omp ) {
727  if ( __kmp_str_match( "ACTIVE", 1, value ) ) {
728  __kmp_library = library_turnaround;
729  } else if ( __kmp_str_match( "PASSIVE", 1, value ) ) {
730  __kmp_library = library_throughput;
731  } else {
732  KMP_WARNING( StgInvalidValue, name, value );
733  }; // if
734  } else {
735  if ( __kmp_str_match( "serial", 1, value ) ) { /* S */
736  __kmp_library = library_serial;
737  } else if ( __kmp_str_match( "throughput", 2, value ) ) { /* TH */
738  __kmp_library = library_throughput;
739  } else if ( __kmp_str_match( "turnaround", 2, value ) ) { /* TU */
740  __kmp_library = library_turnaround;
741  } else if ( __kmp_str_match( "dedicated", 1, value ) ) { /* D */
742  __kmp_library = library_turnaround;
743  } else if ( __kmp_str_match( "multiuser", 1, value ) ) { /* M */
744  __kmp_library = library_throughput;
745  } else {
746  KMP_WARNING( StgInvalidValue, name, value );
747  }; // if
748  }; // if
749  __kmp_aux_set_library( __kmp_library );
750 
751 } // __kmp_stg_parse_wait_policy
752 
753 static void
754 __kmp_stg_print_wait_policy( kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data ) {
755 
756  kmp_stg_wp_data_t * wait = (kmp_stg_wp_data_t *) data;
757  char const * value = NULL;
758 
759  if ( wait->omp ) {
760  switch ( __kmp_library ) {
761  case library_turnaround : {
762  value = "ACTIVE";
763  } break;
764  case library_throughput : {
765  value = "PASSIVE";
766  } break;
767  }; // switch
768  } else {
769  switch ( __kmp_library ) {
770  case library_serial : {
771  value = "serial";
772  } break;
773  case library_turnaround : {
774  value = "turnaround";
775  } break;
776  case library_throughput : {
777  value = "throughput";
778  } break;
779  }; // switch
780  }; // if
781  if ( value != NULL ) {
782  __kmp_stg_print_str( buffer, name, value );
783  }; // if
784 
785 } // __kmp_stg_print_wait_policy

969 static void
970 __kmp_parse_nested_num_threads( const char *var, const char *env, kmp_nested_nthreads_t *nth_array )
971 {
972  const char *next = env;
973  const char *scan = next;
974 
975  int total = 0; // Count elements that were set. It'll be used as an array size
976  int prev_comma = FALSE; // For correct processing sequential commas
977 
978  // Count the number of values in the env. var string
979  for ( ; ; ) {
980  SKIP_WS( next );
981 
982  if ( *next == '\0' ) {
983  break;
984  }
985  // Next character is not an integer or not a comma => end of list
986  if ( ( ( *next < '0' ) || ( *next > '9' ) ) && ( *next !=',') ) {
987  KMP_WARNING( NthSyntaxError, var, env );
988  return;
989  }
990  // The next character is ','
991  if ( *next == ',' ) {
992  // ',' is the fisrt character
993  if ( total == 0 || prev_comma ) {
994  total++;
995  }
996  prev_comma = TRUE;
997  next++; //skip ','
998  SKIP_WS( next );
999  }
1000  // Next character is a digit
1001  if ( *next >= '0' && *next <= '9' ) {
1002  prev_comma = FALSE;
1003  SKIP_DIGITS( next );
1004  total++;
1005  const char *tmp = next;
1006  SKIP_WS( tmp );
1007  if ( ( *next == ' ' || *next == '\t' ) && ( *tmp >= '0' && *tmp <= '9' ) ) {
1008  KMP_WARNING( NthSpacesNotAllowed, var, env );
1009  return;
1010  }
1011  }
1012  }
1013  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( total > 0 );
1014  if( total <= 0 ) {
1015  KMP_WARNING( NthSyntaxError, var, env );
1016  return;
1017  }
1018 
1019  // Check if the nested nthreads array exists
1020  if ( ! nth_array->nth ) {
1021  // Allocate an array of double size
1022  nth_array->nth = ( int * )KMP_INTERNAL_MALLOC( sizeof( int ) * total * 2 );
1023  if ( nth_array->nth == NULL ) {
1024  KMP_FATAL( MemoryAllocFailed );
1025  }
1026  nth_array->size = total * 2;
1027  } else {
1028  if ( nth_array->size < total ) {
1029  // Increase the array size
1030  do {
1031  nth_array->size *= 2;
1032  } while ( nth_array->size < total );
1033 
1034  nth_array->nth = (int *) KMP_INTERNAL_REALLOC(
1035  nth_array->nth, sizeof( int ) * nth_array->size );
1036  if ( nth_array->nth == NULL ) {
1037  KMP_FATAL( MemoryAllocFailed );
1038  }
1039  }
1040  }
1041  nth_array->used = total;
1042  int i = 0;
1043 
1044  prev_comma = FALSE;
1045  total = 0;
1046  // Save values in the array
1047  for ( ; ; ) {
1048  SKIP_WS( scan );
1049  if ( *scan == '\0' ) {
1050  break;
1051  }
1052  // The next character is ','
1053  if ( *scan == ',' ) {
1054  // ',' in the beginning of the list
1055  if ( total == 0 ) {
1056  // The value is supposed to be equal to __kmp_avail_proc but it is unknown at the moment.
1057  // So let's put a placeholder (#threads = 0) to correct it later.
1058  nth_array->nth[i++] = 0;
1059  total++;
1060  }else if ( prev_comma ) {
1061  // Num threads is inherited from the previous level
1062  nth_array->nth[i] = nth_array->nth[i - 1];
1063  i++;
1064  total++;
1065  }
1066  prev_comma = TRUE;
1067  scan++; //skip ','
1068  SKIP_WS( scan );
1069  }
1070  // Next character is a digit
1071  if ( *scan >= '0' && *scan <= '9' ) {
1072  int num;
1073  const char *buf = scan;
1074  char const * msg = NULL;
1075  prev_comma = FALSE;
1076  SKIP_DIGITS( scan );
1077  total++;
1078 
1079  num = __kmp_str_to_int( buf, *scan );
1080  if ( num < KMP_MIN_NTH ) {
1081  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooSmall );
1082  num = KMP_MIN_NTH;
1083  } else if ( num > __kmp_sys_max_nth ) {
1084  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooLarge );
1085  num = __kmp_sys_max_nth;
1086  }
1087  if ( msg != NULL ) {
1088  // Message is not empty. Print warning.
1089  KMP_WARNING( ParseSizeIntWarn, var, env, msg );
1090  KMP_INFORM( Using_int_Value, var, num );
1091  }
1092  nth_array->nth[i++] = num;
1093  }
1094  }
1095 }

1097 static void
1098 __kmp_stg_parse_num_threads( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
1099  // TODO: Remove this option. OMP_NUM_THREADS is a list of positive integers!
1100  if ( ! __kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "all", value, 0 ) ) {
1101  // The array of 1 element
1102  __kmp_nested_nth.nth = ( int* )KMP_INTERNAL_MALLOC( sizeof( int ) );
1103  __kmp_nested_nth.size = __kmp_nested_nth.used = 1;
1104  __kmp_nested_nth.nth[0] = __kmp_dflt_team_nth = __kmp_dflt_team_nth_ub = __kmp_xproc;
1105  } else {
1106  __kmp_parse_nested_num_threads( name, value, & __kmp_nested_nth );
1107  if ( __kmp_nested_nth.nth ) {
1108  __kmp_dflt_team_nth = __kmp_nested_nth.nth[0];
1109  if ( __kmp_dflt_team_nth_ub < __kmp_dflt_team_nth ) {
1110  __kmp_dflt_team_nth_ub = __kmp_dflt_team_nth;
1111  }
1112  }
1113  }; // if

1393 // TODO: Remove __kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name varibale, remove loops from parse and print
1394 // functions, pass required info through data argument.
1395 
1396 static void
1397 __kmp_stg_parse_barrier_branch_bit( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
1398  const char *var;
1399 
1400  /* ---------- Barrier branch bit control ------------ */
1401  for ( int i=bs_plain_barrier; i<bs_last_barrier; i++ ) {
1402  var = __kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name[ i ];
1403  if ( ( strcmp( var, name) == 0 ) && ( value != 0 ) ) {
1404  char *comma;
1405 
1406  comma = (char *) strchr( value, ',' );
1407  __kmp_barrier_gather_branch_bits[ i ] = ( kmp_uint32 ) __kmp_str_to_int( value, ',' );
1408  /* is there a specified release parameter? */
1409  if ( comma == NULL ) {
1410  __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits[ i ] = __kmp_barrier_release_bb_dflt;
1411  } else {
1412  __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits[ i ] = (kmp_uint32) __kmp_str_to_int( comma + 1, 0 );
1413 
1414  if ( __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits[ i ] > KMP_MAX_BRANCH_BITS ) {
1415  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( BarrReleaseValueInvalid, name, comma + 1 ), __kmp_msg_null );
1416  __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits[ i ] = __kmp_barrier_release_bb_dflt;
1417  }
1418  }
1419  if ( __kmp_barrier_gather_branch_bits[ i ] > KMP_MAX_BRANCH_BITS ) {
1420  KMP_WARNING( BarrGatherValueInvalid, name, value );
1421  KMP_INFORM( Using_uint_Value, name, __kmp_barrier_gather_bb_dflt );
1422  __kmp_barrier_gather_branch_bits[ i ] = __kmp_barrier_gather_bb_dflt;
1423  }
1424  }
1425  K_DIAG(1, ("%s == %d,%d\n", __kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name[ i ], \
1426  __kmp_barrier_gather_branch_bits [ i ], \
1427  __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits [ i ]))
1428  }
1429 } // __kmp_stg_parse_barrier_branch_bit
1430 
1431 static void
1432 __kmp_stg_print_barrier_branch_bit( kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data ) {
1433  const char *var;
1434  for ( int i=bs_plain_barrier; i<bs_last_barrier; i++ ) {
1435  var = __kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name[ i ];
1436  if ( strcmp( var, name) == 0 ) {
1437  if( __kmp_env_format ) {
1438  KMP_STR_BUF_PRINT_NAME_EX(__kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name[ i ]);
1439  } else {
1440  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, " %s='", __kmp_barrier_branch_bit_env_name[ i ] );
1441  }
1442  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, "%d,%d'\n", __kmp_barrier_gather_branch_bits [ i ], __kmp_barrier_release_branch_bits [ i ]);
1443  }
1444  }
1445 } // __kmp_stg_print_barrier_branch_bit

1448 // -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1449 // KMP_PLAIN_BARRIER_PATTERN, KMP_FORKJOIN_BARRIER_PATTERN, KMP_REDUCTION_BARRIER_PATTERN
1450 // -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1451 
1452 // TODO: Remove __kmp_barrier_pattern_name variable, remove loops from parse and print functions,
1453 // pass required data to functions through data argument.
1454 
1455 static void
1456 __kmp_stg_parse_barrier_pattern( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
1457  const char *var;
1458  /* ---------- Barrier method control ------------ */
1459 
1460  for ( int i=bs_plain_barrier; i<bs_last_barrier; i++ ) {
1461  var = __kmp_barrier_pattern_env_name[ i ];
1462 
1463  if ( ( strcmp ( var, name ) == 0 ) && ( value != 0 ) ) {
1464  int j;
1465  char *comma = (char *) strchr( value, ',' );
1466 
1467  /* handle first parameter: gather pattern */
1468  for ( j = bp_linear_bar; j<bp_last_bar; j++ ) {
1469  if (__kmp_match_with_sentinel( __kmp_barrier_pattern_name[j], value, 1, ',' )) {
1470  __kmp_barrier_gather_pattern[ i ] = (kmp_bar_pat_e) j;
1471  break;
1472  }
1473  }
1474  if ( j == bp_last_bar ) {
1475  KMP_WARNING( BarrGatherValueInvalid, name, value );
1476  KMP_INFORM( Using_str_Value, name, __kmp_barrier_pattern_name[ bp_linear_bar ] );
1477  }
1478 
1479  /* handle second parameter: release pattern */
1480  if ( comma != NULL ) {
1481  for ( j = bp_linear_bar; j < bp_last_bar; j++ ) {
1482  if ( __kmp_str_match( __kmp_barrier_pattern_name[j], 1, comma + 1 ) ) {
1483  __kmp_barrier_release_pattern[ i ] = (kmp_bar_pat_e) j;
1484  break;
1485  }
1486  }
1487  if (j == bp_last_bar) {
1488  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( BarrReleaseValueInvalid, name, comma + 1 ), __kmp_msg_null );
1489  KMP_INFORM( Using_str_Value, name, __kmp_barrier_pattern_name[ bp_linear_bar ] );
1490  }
1491  }
1492  }
1493  }
1494 } // __kmp_stg_parse_barrier_pattern
1495 
1496 static void
1497 __kmp_stg_print_barrier_pattern( kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data ) {
1498  const char *var;
1499  for ( int i=bs_plain_barrier; i<bs_last_barrier; i++ ) {
1500  var = __kmp_barrier_pattern_env_name[ i ];
1501  if ( strcmp ( var, name ) == 0 ) {
1502  int j = __kmp_barrier_gather_pattern [ i ];
1503  int k = __kmp_barrier_release_pattern [ i ];
1504  if( __kmp_env_format ) {
1505  KMP_STR_BUF_PRINT_NAME_EX(__kmp_barrier_pattern_env_name[ i ]);
1506  } else {
1507  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, " %s='", __kmp_barrier_pattern_env_name[ i ] );
1508  }
1509  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, "%s,%s'\n", __kmp_barrier_pattern_name [ j ], __kmp_barrier_pattern_name [ k ]);
1510  }
1511  }
1512 } // __kmp_stg_print_barrier_pattern

1561 // -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1562 
1563 static void
1564 __kmp_stg_parse_force_reduction( char const * name, char const * value, void * data )
1565 {
1566  kmp_stg_fr_data_t * reduction = (kmp_stg_fr_data_t *) data;
1567  int rc;
1568 
1569  rc = __kmp_stg_check_rivals( name, value, reduction->rivals );
1570  if ( rc ) {
1571  return;
1572  }; // if
1573  if ( reduction->force ) {
1574  if( value != 0 ) {
1575  if( __kmp_str_match( "critical", 0, value ) )
1576  __kmp_force_reduction_method = critical_reduce_block;
1577  else if( __kmp_str_match( "atomic", 0, value ) )
1578  __kmp_force_reduction_method = atomic_reduce_block;
1579  else if( __kmp_str_match( "tree", 0, value ) )
1580  __kmp_force_reduction_method = tree_reduce_block;
1581  else {
1582  KMP_FATAL( UnknownForceReduction, name, value );
1583  }
1584  }
1585  } else {
1586  __kmp_stg_parse_bool( name, value, & __kmp_determ_red );
1587  if( __kmp_determ_red ) {
1588  __kmp_force_reduction_method = tree_reduce_block;
1589  } else {
1590  __kmp_force_reduction_method = reduction_method_not_defined;
1591  }
1592  }
1593  K_DIAG( 1, ( "__kmp_force_reduction_method == %d\n", __kmp_force_reduction_method ) );
1594 } // __kmp_stg_parse_force_reduction
1595

1597 __kmp_stg_print_force_reduction( kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data ) {
1598 
1599  kmp_stg_fr_data_t * reduction = (kmp_stg_fr_data_t *) data;
1600  if ( reduction->force ) {
1601  if( __kmp_force_reduction_method == critical_reduce_block) {
1602  __kmp_stg_print_str( buffer, name, "critical");
1603  } else if ( __kmp_force_reduction_method == atomic_reduce_block ) {
1604  __kmp_stg_print_str( buffer, name, "atomic");
1605  } else if ( __kmp_force_reduction_method == tree_reduce_block ) {
1606  __kmp_stg_print_str( buffer, name, "tree");
1607  } else {
1608  if( __kmp_env_format ) {

1612  }
1613  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, ": %s\n", KMP_I18N_STR( NotDefined ) );
1614  }
1615  } else {
1616  __kmp_stg_print_bool( buffer, name, __kmp_determ_red );
1617  }

1682 
1683 #if KMP_AFFINITY_SUPPORTED
1684 //
1685 // Parse the proc id list. Return TRUE if successful, FALSE otherwise.
1686 //
1687 static int
1688 __kmp_parse_affinity_proc_id_list( const char *var, const char *env,
1689  const char **nextEnv, char **proclist )
1690 {
1691  const char *scan = env;
1692  const char *next = scan;
1693  int empty = TRUE;
1694 
1695  *proclist = NULL;
1696 
1697  for (;;) {
1698  int start, end, stride;
1699 
1700  SKIP_WS(scan);
1701  next = scan;
1702  if (*next == '\0') {
1703  break;
1704  }
1705 
1706  if (*next == '{') {
1707  int num;
1708  next++; // skip '{'
1709  SKIP_WS(next);
1710  scan = next;
1711 
1712  //
1713  // Read the first integer in the set.
1714  //
1715  if ((*next < '0') || (*next > '9')) {
1716  KMP_WARNING( AffSyntaxError, var );
1717  return FALSE;
1718  }
1719  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
1720  num = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
1721  KMP_ASSERT(num >= 0);
1722 
1723  for (;;) {
1724  //
1725  // Check for end of set.
1726  //
1727  SKIP_WS(next);
1728  if (*next == '}') {
1729  next++; // skip '}'
1730  break;
1731  }
1732 
1733  //
1734  // Skip optional comma.
1735  //
1736  if (*next == ',') {
1737  next++;
1738  }
1739  SKIP_WS(next);
1740 
1741  //
1742  // Read the next integer in the set.
1743  //
1744  scan = next;
1745  if ((*next < '0') || (*next > '9')) {
1746  KMP_WARNING( AffSyntaxError, var );
1747  return FALSE;
1748  }
1749 
1750  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
1751  num = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
1752  KMP_ASSERT(num >= 0);
1753  }
1754  empty = FALSE;
1755 
1756  SKIP_WS(next);
1757  if (*next == ',') {
1758  next++;
1759  }
1760  scan = next;
1761  continue;
1762  }
1763 
1764  //
1765  // Next character is not an integer => end of list
1766  //
1767  if ((*next < '0') || (*next > '9')) {
1768  if (empty) {
1769  KMP_WARNING( AffSyntaxError, var );
1770  return FALSE;
1771  }
1772  break;
1773  }
1774 
1775  //
1776  // Read the first integer.
1777  //
1778  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
1779  start = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
1780  KMP_ASSERT(start >= 0);
1781  SKIP_WS(next);
1782 
1783  //
1784  // If this isn't a range, then go on.
1785  //
1786  if (*next != '-') {
1787  empty = FALSE;
1788 
1789  //
1790  // Skip optional comma.
1791  //
1792  if (*next == ',') {
1793  next++;
1794  }
1795  scan = next;
1796  continue;
1797  }
1798 
1799  //
1800  // This is a range. Skip over the '-' and read in the 2nd int.
1801  //
1802  next++; // skip '-'
1803  SKIP_WS(next);
1804  scan = next;
1805  if ((*next < '0') || (*next > '9')) {
1806  KMP_WARNING( AffSyntaxError, var );
1807  return FALSE;
1808  }
1809  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
1810  end = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
1811  KMP_ASSERT(end >= 0);
1812 
1813  //
1814  // Check for a stride parameter
1815  //
1816  stride = 1;
1817  SKIP_WS(next);
1818  if (*next == ':') {
1819  //
1820  // A stride is specified. Skip over the ':" and read the 3rd int.
1821  //
1822  int sign = +1;
1823  next++; // skip ':'
1824  SKIP_WS(next);
1825  scan = next;
1826  if (*next == '-') {
1827  sign = -1;
1828  next++;
1829  SKIP_WS(next);
1830  scan = next;
1831  }
1832  if ((*next < '0') || (*next > '9')) {
1833  KMP_WARNING( AffSyntaxError, var );
1834  return FALSE;
1835  }
1836  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
1837  stride = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
1838  KMP_ASSERT(stride >= 0);
1839  stride *= sign;
1840  }
1841 
1842  //
1843  // Do some range checks.
1844  //
1845  if (stride == 0) {
1846  KMP_WARNING( AffZeroStride, var );
1847  return FALSE;
1848  }
1849  if (stride > 0) {
1850  if (start > end) {
1851  KMP_WARNING( AffStartGreaterEnd, var, start, end );
1852  return FALSE;
1853  }
1854  }
1855  else {
1856  if (start < end) {
1857  KMP_WARNING( AffStrideLessZero, var, start, end );
1858  return FALSE;
1859  }
1860  }
1861  if ((end - start) / stride > 65536 ) {
1862  KMP_WARNING( AffRangeTooBig, var, end, start, stride );
1863  return FALSE;
1864  }
1865 
1866  empty = FALSE;
1867 
1868  //
1869  // Skip optional comma.
1870  //
1871  SKIP_WS(next);
1872  if (*next == ',') {
1873  next++;
1874  }
1875  scan = next;
1876  }
1877 
1878  *nextEnv = next;
1879 
1880  {
1881  int len = next - env;
1882  char *retlist = (char *)__kmp_allocate((len + 1) * sizeof(char));
1883  KMP_MEMCPY_S(retlist, (len+1)*sizeof(char), env, len * sizeof(char));
1884  retlist[len] = '\0';
1885  *proclist = retlist;
1886  }
1887  return TRUE;
1888 }

1891 //
1892 // If KMP_AFFINITY is specified without a type, then
1893 // __kmp_affinity_notype should point to its setting.
1894 //
1895 static kmp_setting_t *__kmp_affinity_notype = NULL;

1897 static void
1898 __kmp_parse_affinity_env( char const * name, char const * value,
1899  enum affinity_type * out_type,
1900  char ** out_proclist,
1901  int * out_verbose,
1902  int * out_warn,
1903  int * out_respect,
1904  enum affinity_gran * out_gran,
1905  int * out_gran_levels,
1906  int * out_dups,
1907  int * out_compact,
1908  int * out_offset
1909 )
1910 {
1911  char * buffer = NULL; // Copy of env var value.
1912  char * buf = NULL; // Buffer for strtok_r() function.
1913  char * next = NULL; // end of token / start of next.
1914  const char * start; // start of current token (for err msgs)
1915  int count = 0; // Counter of parsed integer numbers.
1916  int number[ 2 ]; // Parsed numbers.
1917 
1918  // Guards.
1919  int type = 0;
1920  int proclist = 0;
1921  int max_proclist = 0;
1922  int verbose = 0;
1923  int warnings = 0;
1924  int respect = 0;
1925  int gran = 0;
1926  int dups = 0;
1927 
1928  KMP_ASSERT( value != NULL );
1929 
1930  if ( TCR_4(__kmp_init_middle) ) {
1931  KMP_WARNING( EnvMiddleWarn, name );
1932  __kmp_env_toPrint( name, 0 );
1933  return;
1934  }
1935  __kmp_env_toPrint( name, 1 );
1936 
1937  buffer = __kmp_str_format( "%s", value ); // Copy env var to keep original intact.
1938  buf = buffer;
1939  SKIP_WS(buf);
1940 
1941  // Helper macros.
1942 
1943  //
1944  // If we see a parse error, emit a warning and scan to the next ",".
1945  //
1946  // FIXME - there's got to be a better way to print an error
1947  // message, hopefully without overwritting peices of buf.
1948  //
1949  #define EMIT_WARN(skip,errlist) \
1950  { \
1951  char ch; \
1952  if (skip) { \
1953  SKIP_TO(next, ','); \
1954  } \
1955  ch = *next; \
1956  *next = '\0'; \
1957  KMP_WARNING errlist; \
1958  *next = ch; \
1959  if (skip) { \
1960  if (ch == ',') next++; \
1961  } \
1962  buf = next; \
1963  }
1964 
1965  #define _set_param(_guard,_var,_val) \
1966  { \
1967  if ( _guard == 0 ) { \
1968  _var = _val; \
1969  } else { \
1970  EMIT_WARN( FALSE, ( AffParamDefined, name, start ) ); \
1971  }; \
1972  ++ _guard; \
1973  }
1974 
1975  #define set_type(val) _set_param( type, *out_type, val )
1976  #define set_verbose(val) _set_param( verbose, *out_verbose, val )
1977  #define set_warnings(val) _set_param( warnings, *out_warn, val )
1978  #define set_respect(val) _set_param( respect, *out_respect, val )
1979  #define set_dups(val) _set_param( dups, *out_dups, val )
1980  #define set_proclist(val) _set_param( proclist, *out_proclist, val )
1981 
1982  #define set_gran(val,levels) \
1983  { \
1984  if ( gran == 0 ) { \
1985  *out_gran = val; \
1986  *out_gran_levels = levels; \
1987  } else { \
1988  EMIT_WARN( FALSE, ( AffParamDefined, name, start ) ); \
1989  }; \
1990  ++ gran; \
1991  }
1992 
1993 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
1994  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( ( __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types != NULL )
1995  && ( __kmp_nested_proc_bind.used > 0 ) );
1996 # endif
1997 
1998  while ( *buf != '\0' ) {
1999  start = next = buf;
2000 
2001  if (__kmp_match_str("none", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2002  set_type( affinity_none );
2003 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2004  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_false;
2005 # endif
2006  buf = next;
2007  } else if (__kmp_match_str("scatter", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2008  set_type( affinity_scatter );
2009 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2010  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2011 # endif
2012  buf = next;
2013  } else if (__kmp_match_str("compact", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2014  set_type( affinity_compact );
2015 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2016  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2017 # endif
2018  buf = next;
2019  } else if (__kmp_match_str("logical", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2020  set_type( affinity_logical );
2021 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2022  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2023 # endif
2024  buf = next;
2025  } else if (__kmp_match_str("physical", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2026  set_type( affinity_physical );
2027 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2028  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2029 # endif
2030  buf = next;
2031  } else if (__kmp_match_str("explicit", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2032  set_type( affinity_explicit );
2033 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2034  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2035 # endif
2036  buf = next;
2037  } else if (__kmp_match_str("balanced", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2038  set_type( affinity_balanced );
2039 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2040  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_intel;
2041 # endif
2042  buf = next;
2043  } else if (__kmp_match_str("disabled", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2044  set_type( affinity_disabled );
2045 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
2046  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_false;
2047 # endif
2048  buf = next;
2049  } else if (__kmp_match_str("verbose", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2050  set_verbose( TRUE );
2051  buf = next;
2052  } else if (__kmp_match_str("noverbose", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2053  set_verbose( FALSE );
2054  buf = next;
2055  } else if (__kmp_match_str("warnings", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2056  set_warnings( TRUE );
2057  buf = next;
2058  } else if (__kmp_match_str("nowarnings", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2059  set_warnings( FALSE );
2060  buf = next;
2061  } else if (__kmp_match_str("respect", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2062  set_respect( TRUE );
2063  buf = next;
2064  } else if (__kmp_match_str("norespect", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2065  set_respect( FALSE );
2066  buf = next;
2067  } else if (__kmp_match_str("duplicates", buf, (const char **)&next)
2068  || __kmp_match_str("dups", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2069  set_dups( TRUE );
2070  buf = next;
2071  } else if (__kmp_match_str("noduplicates", buf, (const char **)&next)
2072  || __kmp_match_str("nodups", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2073  set_dups( FALSE );
2074  buf = next;
2075  } else if (__kmp_match_str("granularity", buf, (const char **)&next)
2076  || __kmp_match_str("gran", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2077  SKIP_WS(next);
2078  if (*next != '=') {
2079  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2080  continue;
2081  }
2082  next++; // skip '='
2083  SKIP_WS(next);
2084 
2085  buf = next;
2086  if (__kmp_match_str("fine", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2087  set_gran( affinity_gran_fine, -1 );
2088  buf = next;
2089  } else if (__kmp_match_str("thread", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2090  set_gran( affinity_gran_thread, -1 );
2091  buf = next;
2092  } else if (__kmp_match_str("core", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2093  set_gran( affinity_gran_core, -1 );
2094  buf = next;
2095  } else if (__kmp_match_str("package", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2096  set_gran( affinity_gran_package, -1 );
2097  buf = next;
2098  } else if (__kmp_match_str("node", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2099  set_gran( affinity_gran_node, -1 );
2100  buf = next;
2101 # if KMP_GROUP_AFFINITY
2102  } else if (__kmp_match_str("group", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2103  set_gran( affinity_gran_group, -1 );
2104  buf = next;
2105 # endif /* KMP_GROUP AFFINITY */
2106  } else if ((*buf >= '0') && (*buf <= '9')) {
2107  int n;
2108  next = buf;
2109  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2110  n = __kmp_str_to_int( buf, *next );
2111  KMP_ASSERT(n >= 0);
2112  buf = next;
2113  set_gran( affinity_gran_default, n );
2114  } else {
2115  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2116  continue;
2117  }
2118  } else if (__kmp_match_str("proclist", buf, (const char **)&next)) {
2119  char *temp_proclist;
2120 
2121  SKIP_WS(next);
2122  if (*next != '=') {
2123  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2124  continue;
2125  }
2126  next++; // skip '='
2127  SKIP_WS(next);
2128  if (*next != '[') {
2129  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2130  continue;
2131  }
2132  next++; // skip '['
2133  buf = next;
2134  if (! __kmp_parse_affinity_proc_id_list(name, buf,
2135  (const char **)&next, &temp_proclist)) {
2136  //
2137  // warning already emitted.
2138  //
2139  SKIP_TO(next, ']');
2140  if (*next == ']') next++;
2141  SKIP_TO(next, ',');
2142  if (*next == ',') next++;
2143  buf = next;
2144  continue;
2145  }
2146  if (*next != ']') {
2147  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2148  continue;
2149  }
2150  next++; // skip ']'
2151  set_proclist( temp_proclist );
2152  } else if ((*buf >= '0') && (*buf <= '9')) {
2153  // Parse integer numbers -- permute and offset.
2154  int n;
2155  next = buf;
2156  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2157  n = __kmp_str_to_int( buf, *next );
2158  KMP_ASSERT(n >= 0);
2159  buf = next;
2160  if ( count < 2 ) {
2161  number[ count ] = n;
2162  } else {
2163  KMP_WARNING( AffManyParams, name, start );
2164  }; // if
2165  ++ count;
2166  } else {
2167  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( AffInvalidParam, name, start ) );
2168  continue;
2169  }
2170 
2171  SKIP_WS(next);
2172  if (*next == ',') {
2173  next++;
2174  SKIP_WS(next);
2175  }
2176  else if (*next != '\0') {
2177  const char *temp = next;
2178  EMIT_WARN( TRUE, ( ParseExtraCharsWarn, name, temp ) );
2179  continue;
2180  }
2181  buf = next;
2182  } // while
2183 
2184  #undef EMIT_WARN
2185  #undef _set_param
2186  #undef set_type
2187  #undef set_verbose
2188  #undef set_warnings
2189  #undef set_respect
2190  #undef set_granularity
2191 
2192  KMP_INTERNAL_FREE( buffer );
2193 
2194  if ( proclist ) {
2195  if ( ! type ) {
2196  KMP_WARNING( AffProcListNoType, name );
2197  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_explicit;
2198  }
2199  else if ( __kmp_affinity_type != affinity_explicit ) {
2200  KMP_WARNING( AffProcListNotExplicit, name );
2201  KMP_ASSERT( *out_proclist != NULL );
2202  KMP_INTERNAL_FREE( *out_proclist );
2203  *out_proclist = NULL;
2204  }
2205  }
2206  switch ( *out_type ) {
2207  case affinity_logical:
2208  case affinity_physical: {
2209  if ( count > 0 ) {
2210  *out_offset = number[ 0 ];
2211  }; // if
2212  if ( count > 1 ) {
2213  KMP_WARNING( AffManyParamsForLogic, name, number[ 1 ] );
2214  }; // if
2215  } break;
2216  case affinity_balanced: {
2217  if ( count > 0 ) {
2218  *out_compact = number[ 0 ];
2219  }; // if
2220  if ( count > 1 ) {
2221  *out_offset = number[ 1 ];
2222  }; // if
2223 
2224  if ( __kmp_affinity_gran == affinity_gran_default ) {
2225 #if KMP_ARCH_X86_64 && (KMP_OS_LINUX || KMP_OS_WINDOWS)
2226  if( __kmp_mic_type != non_mic ) {
2227  if( __kmp_affinity_verbose || __kmp_affinity_warnings ) {
2228  KMP_WARNING( AffGranUsing, "KMP_AFFINITY", "fine" );
2229  }
2230  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_fine;
2231  } else
2232 #endif
2233  {
2234  if( __kmp_affinity_verbose || __kmp_affinity_warnings ) {
2235  KMP_WARNING( AffGranUsing, "KMP_AFFINITY", "core" );
2236  }
2237  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_core;
2238  }
2239  }
2240  } break;
2241  case affinity_scatter:
2242  case affinity_compact: {
2243  if ( count > 0 ) {
2244  *out_compact = number[ 0 ];
2245  }; // if
2246  if ( count > 1 ) {
2247  *out_offset = number[ 1 ];
2248  }; // if
2249  } break;
2250  case affinity_explicit: {
2251  if ( *out_proclist == NULL ) {
2252  KMP_WARNING( AffNoProcList, name );
2253  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_none;
2254  }
2255  if ( count > 0 ) {
2256  KMP_WARNING( AffNoParam, name, "explicit" );
2257  }
2258  } break;
2259  case affinity_none: {
2260  if ( count > 0 ) {
2261  KMP_WARNING( AffNoParam, name, "none" );
2262  }; // if
2263  } break;
2264  case affinity_disabled: {
2265  if ( count > 0 ) {
2266  KMP_WARNING( AffNoParam, name, "disabled" );
2267  }; // if
2268  } break;
2269  case affinity_default: {
2270  if ( count > 0 ) {
2271  KMP_WARNING( AffNoParam, name, "default" );
2272  }; // if
2273  } break;
2274  default: {
2275  KMP_ASSERT( 0 );
2276  };
2277  }; // switch
2278 } // __kmp_parse_affinity_env

2458 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2459 
2460 The OMP_PLACES proc id list parser. Here is the grammar:
2461 
2462 place_list := place
2463 place_list := place , place_list
2464 place := num
2465 place := place : num
2466 place := place : num : signed
2467 place := { subplacelist }
2468 place := ! place // (lowest priority)
2469 subplace_list := subplace
2470 subplace_list := subplace , subplace_list
2471 subplace := num
2472 subplace := num : num
2473 subplace := num : num : signed
2474 signed := num
2475 signed := + signed
2476 signed := - signed
2477 
2478 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
2479 
2480 static int
2481 __kmp_parse_subplace_list( const char *var, const char **scan )
2482 {
2483  const char *next;
2484 
2485  for (;;) {
2486  int start, count, stride;
2487 
2488  //
2489  // Read in the starting proc id
2490  //
2491  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2492  if ((**scan < '0') || (**scan > '9')) {
2493  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2494  return FALSE;
2495  }
2496  next = *scan;
2497  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2498  start = __kmp_str_to_int(*scan, *next);
2499  KMP_ASSERT(start >= 0);
2500  *scan = next;
2501 
2502  //
2503  // valid follow sets are ',' ':' and '}'
2504  //
2505  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2506  if (**scan == '}') {
2507  break;
2508  }
2509  if (**scan == ',') {
2510  (*scan)++; // skip ','
2511  continue;
2512  }
2513  if (**scan != ':') {
2514  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2515  return FALSE;
2516  }
2517  (*scan)++; // skip ':'
2518 
2519  //
2520  // Read count parameter
2521  //
2522  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2523  if ((**scan < '0') || (**scan > '9')) {
2524  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2525  return FALSE;
2526  }
2527  next = *scan;
2528  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2529  count = __kmp_str_to_int(*scan, *next);
2530  KMP_ASSERT(count >= 0);
2531  *scan = next;
2532 
2533  //
2534  // valid follow sets are ',' ':' and '}'
2535  //
2536  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2537  if (**scan == '}') {
2538  break;
2539  }
2540  if (**scan == ',') {
2541  (*scan)++; // skip ','
2542  continue;
2543  }
2544  if (**scan != ':') {
2545  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2546  return FALSE;
2547  }
2548  (*scan)++; // skip ':'
2549 
2550  //
2551  // Read stride parameter
2552  //
2553  int sign = +1;
2554  for (;;) {
2555  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2556  if (**scan == '+') {
2557  (*scan)++; // skip '+'
2558  continue;
2559  }
2560  if (**scan == '-') {
2561  sign *= -1;
2562  (*scan)++; // skip '-'
2563  continue;
2564  }
2565  break;
2566  }
2567  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2568  if ((**scan < '0') || (**scan > '9')) {
2569  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2570  return FALSE;
2571  }
2572  next = *scan;
2573  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2574  stride = __kmp_str_to_int(*scan, *next);
2575  KMP_ASSERT(stride >= 0);
2576  *scan = next;
2577  stride *= sign;
2578 
2579  //
2580  // valid follow sets are ',' and '}'
2581  //
2582  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2583  if (**scan == '}') {
2584  break;
2585  }
2586  if (**scan == ',') {
2587  (*scan)++; // skip ','
2588  continue;
2589  }
2590 
2591  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2592  return FALSE;
2593  }
2594  return TRUE;
2595 }

2597 static int
2598 __kmp_parse_place( const char *var, const char ** scan )
2599 {
2600  const char *next;
2601 
2602  //
2603  // valid follow sets are '{' '!' and num
2604  //
2605  SKIP_WS(*scan);
2606  if (**scan == '{') {
2607  (*scan)++; // skip '{'
2608  if (! __kmp_parse_subplace_list(var, scan)) {
2609  return FALSE;
2610  }
2611  if (**scan != '}') {
2612  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2613  return FALSE;
2614  }
2615  (*scan)++; // skip '}'
2616  }
2617  else if (**scan == '!') {
2618  (*scan)++; // skip '!'
2619  return __kmp_parse_place(var, scan); //'!' has lower precedence than ':'
2620  }
2621  else if ((**scan >= '0') && (**scan <= '9')) {
2622  next = *scan;
2623  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2624  int proc = __kmp_str_to_int(*scan, *next);
2625  KMP_ASSERT(proc >= 0);
2626  *scan = next;
2627  }
2628  else {
2629  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2630  return FALSE;
2631  }
2632  return TRUE;
2633 }

2635 static int
2636 __kmp_parse_place_list( const char *var, const char *env, char **place_list )
2637 {
2638  const char *scan = env;
2639  const char *next = scan;
2640 
2641  for (;;) {
2642  int start, count, stride;
2643 
2644  if (! __kmp_parse_place(var, &scan)) {
2645  return FALSE;
2646  }
2647 
2648  //
2649  // valid follow sets are ',' ':' and EOL
2650  //
2651  SKIP_WS(scan);
2652  if (*scan == '\0') {
2653  break;
2654  }
2655  if (*scan == ',') {
2656  scan++; // skip ','
2657  continue;
2658  }
2659  if (*scan != ':') {
2660  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2661  return FALSE;
2662  }
2663  scan++; // skip ':'
2664 
2665  //
2666  // Read count parameter
2667  //
2668  SKIP_WS(scan);
2669  if ((*scan < '0') || (*scan > '9')) {
2670  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2671  return FALSE;
2672  }
2673  next = scan;
2674  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2675  count = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
2676  KMP_ASSERT(count >= 0);
2677  scan = next;
2678 
2679  //
2680  // valid follow sets are ',' ':' and EOL
2681  //
2682  SKIP_WS(scan);
2683  if (*scan == '\0') {
2684  break;
2685  }
2686  if (*scan == ',') {
2687  scan++; // skip ','
2688  continue;
2689  }
2690  if (*scan != ':') {
2691  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2692  return FALSE;
2693  }
2694  scan++; // skip ':'
2695 
2696  //
2697  // Read stride parameter
2698  //
2699  int sign = +1;
2700  for (;;) {
2701  SKIP_WS(scan);
2702  if (*scan == '+') {
2703  scan++; // skip '+'
2704  continue;
2705  }
2706  if (*scan == '-') {
2707  sign *= -1;
2708  scan++; // skip '-'
2709  continue;
2710  }
2711  break;
2712  }
2713  SKIP_WS(scan);
2714  if ((*scan < '0') || (*scan > '9')) {
2715  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2716  return FALSE;
2717  }
2718  next = scan;
2719  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2720  stride = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
2721  KMP_ASSERT(stride >= 0);
2722  scan = next;
2723  stride *= sign;
2724 
2725  //
2726  // valid follow sets are ',' and EOL
2727  //
2728  SKIP_WS(scan);
2729  if (*scan == '\0') {
2730  break;
2731  }
2732  if (*scan == ',') {
2733  scan++; // skip ','
2734  continue;
2735  }
2736 
2737  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, var, "\"threads\"" );
2738  return FALSE;
2739  }
2740 
2741  {
2742  int len = scan - env;
2743  char *retlist = (char *)__kmp_allocate((len + 1) * sizeof(char));
2744  KMP_MEMCPY_S(retlist, (len+1)*sizeof(char), env, len * sizeof(char));
2745  retlist[len] = '\0';
2746  *place_list = retlist;
2747  }
2748  return TRUE;

2751 static void
2752 __kmp_stg_parse_places( char const * name, char const * value, void * data )
2753 {
2754  int count;
2755  const char *scan = value;
2756  const char *next = scan;
2757  const char *kind = "\"threads\"";
2758  kmp_setting_t **rivals = (kmp_setting_t **) data;
2759  int rc;
2760 
2761  rc = __kmp_stg_check_rivals( name, value, rivals );
2762  if ( rc ) {
2763  return;
2764  }
2765 
2766  //
2767  // If OMP_PROC_BIND is not specified but OMP_PLACES is,
2768  // then let OMP_PROC_BIND default to true.
2769  //
2770  if ( __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] == proc_bind_default ) {
2771  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_true;
2772  }
2773 
2774  //__kmp_affinity_num_places = 0;
2775 
2776  if ( __kmp_match_str( "threads", scan, &next ) ) {
2777  scan = next;
2778  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_compact;
2779  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_thread;
2780  __kmp_affinity_dups = FALSE;
2781  kind = "\"threads\"";
2782  }
2783  else if ( __kmp_match_str( "cores", scan, &next ) ) {
2784  scan = next;
2785  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_compact;
2786  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_core;
2787  __kmp_affinity_dups = FALSE;
2788  kind = "\"cores\"";
2789  }
2790  else if ( __kmp_match_str( "sockets", scan, &next ) ) {
2791  scan = next;
2792  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_compact;
2793  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_package;
2794  __kmp_affinity_dups = FALSE;
2795  kind = "\"sockets\"";
2796  }
2797  else {
2798  if ( __kmp_affinity_proclist != NULL ) {
2799  KMP_INTERNAL_FREE( (void *)__kmp_affinity_proclist );
2800  __kmp_affinity_proclist = NULL;
2801  }
2802  if ( __kmp_parse_place_list( name, value, &__kmp_affinity_proclist ) ) {
2803  __kmp_affinity_type = affinity_explicit;
2804  __kmp_affinity_gran = affinity_gran_fine;
2805  __kmp_affinity_dups = FALSE;
2806  if ( __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] == proc_bind_default ) {
2807  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_true;
2808  }
2809  }
2810  return;
2811  }
2812 
2813  if ( __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] == proc_bind_default ) {
2814  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[0] = proc_bind_true;
2815  }
2816 
2817  SKIP_WS(scan);
2818  if ( *scan == '\0' ) {
2819  return;
2820  }
2821 
2822  //
2823  // Parse option count parameter in parentheses
2824  //
2825  if ( *scan != '(' ) {
2826  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, name, kind );
2827  return;
2828  }
2829  scan++; // skip '('
2830 
2831  SKIP_WS(scan);
2832  next = scan;
2833  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
2834  count = __kmp_str_to_int(scan, *next);
2835  KMP_ASSERT(count >= 0);
2836  scan = next;
2837 
2838  SKIP_WS(scan);
2839  if ( *scan != ')' ) {
2840  KMP_WARNING( SyntaxErrorUsing, name, kind );
2841  return;
2842  }
2843  scan++; // skip ')'
2844 
2845  SKIP_WS(scan);
2846  if ( *scan != '\0' ) {
2847  KMP_WARNING( ParseExtraCharsWarn, name, scan );
2848  }
2849  __kmp_affinity_num_places = count;
2850 }

3207  return;

3210  __kmp_nested_proc_bind.bind_types[i++] = bind;
3211  if ( i >= nelem ) {
3212  break;
3213  }
3214  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( *buf == ',' );
3215  buf++;
3216  SKIP_WS( buf );
3217

3219  // Read next value if it was specified as an integer
3220  //

3222  next = buf;

3225  KMP_ASSERT( num >= 0 );
3226  buf = next;
3227  SKIP_WS( buf );
3228  }
3229  else {
3230  num = -1;
3231  }
3232  }
3233  SKIP_WS( buf );
3234  }

3418 static void
3419 __kmp_stg_parse_schedule( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
3420 
3421  if ( value != NULL ) {
3422  size_t length = KMP_STRLEN( value );
3423  if ( length > INT_MAX ) {
3424  KMP_WARNING( LongValue, name );
3425  } else {
3426  char *semicolon;
3427  if( value[ length - 1 ] == '"' || value[ length -1 ] == '\'' )
3428  KMP_WARNING( UnbalancedQuotes, name );
3429  do {
3430  char sentinel;
3431 
3432  semicolon = (char *) strchr( value, ';' );
3433  if( *value && semicolon != value ) {
3434  char *comma = (char *) strchr( value, ',' );
3435 
3436  if ( comma ) {
3437  ++comma;
3438  sentinel = ',';
3439  } else
3440  sentinel = ';';
3441  if ( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "static", value, sentinel ) ) {
3442  if( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "greedy", comma, ';' ) ) {
3443  __kmp_static = kmp_sch_static_greedy;
3444  continue;
3445  } else if( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "balanced", comma, ';' ) ) {
3446  __kmp_static = kmp_sch_static_balanced;
3447  continue;
3448  }
3449  } else if ( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "guided", value, sentinel ) ) {
3450  if ( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "iterative", comma, ';' ) ) {
3451  __kmp_guided = kmp_sch_guided_iterative_chunked;
3452  continue;
3453  } else if ( !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel( "analytical", comma, ';' ) ) {
3454  /* analytical not allowed for too many threads */
3455  __kmp_guided = kmp_sch_guided_analytical_chunked;
3456  continue;
3457  }
3458  }
3459  KMP_WARNING( InvalidClause, name, value );
3460  } else
3461  KMP_WARNING( EmptyClause, name );
3462  } while ( (value = semicolon ? semicolon + 1 : NULL) );
3463  }
3464  }; // if
3465 
3466 } // __kmp_stg_parse__schedule

3470  if( __kmp_env_format ) {
3471  KMP_STR_BUF_PRINT_NAME_EX(name);
3472  } else {
3473  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, " %s='", name );
3474  }
3475  if ( __kmp_static == kmp_sch_static_greedy ) {
3476  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, "%s", "static,greedy");
3477  } else if ( __kmp_static == kmp_sch_static_balanced ) {
3478  __kmp_str_buf_print ( buffer, "%s", "static,balanced");
3479  }
3480  if ( __kmp_guided == kmp_sch_guided_iterative_chunked ) {
3481  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, ";%s'\n", "guided,iterative");
3482  } else if ( __kmp_guided == kmp_sch_guided_analytical_chunked ) {

3490 
3491 static void
3492 __kmp_stg_parse_omp_schedule( char const * name, char const * value, void * data )
3493 {
3494  size_t length;
3495  if( value ) {
3496  length = KMP_STRLEN( value );
3497  if( length ) {
3498  char *comma = (char *) strchr( value, ',' );
3499  if( value[ length - 1 ] == '"' || value[ length -1 ] == '\'')
3500  KMP_WARNING( UnbalancedQuotes, name );
3501  /* get the specified scheduling style */
3502  if (!__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("dynamic", value, ',')) /* DYNAMIC */
3503  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_dynamic_chunked;
3504  else if (!__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("guided", value, ',')) /* GUIDED */
3505  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_guided_chunked;
3506 // AC: TODO: add AUTO schedule, and pprobably remove TRAPEZOIDAL (OMP 3.0 does not allow it)
3507  else if (!__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("auto", value, ',')) { /* AUTO */
3508  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_auto;
3509  if( comma ) {
3510  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( IgnoreChunk, name, comma ), __kmp_msg_null );
3511  comma = NULL;
3512  }
3513  }
3514  else if (!__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("trapezoidal", value, ',')) /* TRAPEZOIDAL */
3515  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_trapezoidal;
3516  else if (!__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("static", value, ',')) /* STATIC */
3517  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_static;
3518 #ifdef KMP_STATIC_STEAL_ENABLED
3519  else if (KMP_ARCH_X86_64 &&
3520  !__kmp_strcasecmp_with_sentinel("static_steal", value, ','))
3521  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_static_steal;
3522 #endif
3523  else {
3524  KMP_WARNING( StgInvalidValue, name, value );
3525  value = NULL; /* skip processing of comma */
3526  }
3527  if( value && comma ) {
3528  __kmp_env_chunk = TRUE;
3529 
3530  if(__kmp_sched == kmp_sch_static)
3531  __kmp_sched = kmp_sch_static_chunked;
3532  ++comma;
3533  __kmp_chunk = __kmp_str_to_int( comma, 0 );
3534  if ( __kmp_chunk < 1 ) {
3535  __kmp_chunk = KMP_DEFAULT_CHUNK;
3536  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( InvalidChunk, name, comma ), __kmp_msg_null );
3537  KMP_INFORM( Using_int_Value, name, __kmp_chunk );
3538 // AC: next block commented out until KMP_DEFAULT_CHUNK != KMP_MIN_CHUNK (to improve code coverage :)
3539 // The default chunk size is 1 according to standard, thus making KMP_MIN_CHUNK not 1 we would introduce mess:
3540 // wrong chunk becomes 1, but it will be impossible to explicitely set 1, because it becomes KMP_MIN_CHUNK...
3541 // } else if ( __kmp_chunk < KMP_MIN_CHUNK ) {
3542 // __kmp_chunk = KMP_MIN_CHUNK;
3543  } else if ( __kmp_chunk > KMP_MAX_CHUNK ) {
3544  __kmp_chunk = KMP_MAX_CHUNK;
3545  __kmp_msg( kmp_ms_warning, KMP_MSG( LargeChunk, name, comma ), __kmp_msg_null );
3546  KMP_INFORM( Using_int_Value, name, __kmp_chunk );
3547  }
3548  } else
3549  __kmp_env_chunk = FALSE;
3550  } else
3551  KMP_WARNING( EmptyString, name );
3552  }
3553  K_DIAG(1, ("__kmp_static == %d\n", __kmp_static))
3554  K_DIAG(1, ("__kmp_guided == %d\n", __kmp_guided))
3555  K_DIAG(1, ("__kmp_sched == %d\n", __kmp_sched))
3556  K_DIAG(1, ("__kmp_chunk == %d\n", __kmp_chunk))
3557 } // __kmp_stg_parse_omp_schedule

4035 
4036 // Parse out values for the tunable parameters from a string of the form
4037 // KMP_ADAPTIVE_LOCK_PROPS=max_soft_retries[,max_badness]
4038 static void
4039 __kmp_stg_parse_adaptive_lock_props( const char *name, const char *value, void *data )
4040 {
4041  int max_retries = 0;
4042  int max_badness = 0;
4043 
4044  const char *next = value;
4045 
4046  int total = 0; // Count elements that were set. It'll be used as an array size
4047  int prev_comma = FALSE; // For correct processing sequential commas
4048  int i;
4049 
4050  // Save values in the structure __kmp_speculative_backoff_params
4051  // Run only 3 iterations because it is enough to read two values or find a syntax error
4052  for ( i = 0; i < 3 ; i++) {
4053  SKIP_WS( next );
4054 
4055  if ( *next == '\0' ) {
4056  break;
4057  }
4058  // Next character is not an integer or not a comma OR number of values > 2 => end of list
4059  if ( ( ( *next < '0' || *next > '9' ) && *next !=',' ) || total > 2 ) {
4060  KMP_WARNING( EnvSyntaxError, name, value );
4061  return;
4062  }
4063  // The next character is ','
4064  if ( *next == ',' ) {
4065  // ',' is the fisrt character
4066  if ( total == 0 || prev_comma ) {
4067  total++;
4068  }
4069  prev_comma = TRUE;
4070  next++; //skip ','
4071  SKIP_WS( next );
4072  }
4073  // Next character is a digit
4074  if ( *next >= '0' && *next <= '9' ) {
4075  int num;
4076  const char *buf = next;
4077  char const * msg = NULL;
4078  prev_comma = FALSE;
4079  SKIP_DIGITS( next );
4080  total++;
4081 
4082  const char *tmp = next;
4083  SKIP_WS( tmp );
4084  if ( ( *next == ' ' || *next == '\t' ) && ( *tmp >= '0' && *tmp <= '9' ) ) {
4085  KMP_WARNING( EnvSpacesNotAllowed, name, value );
4086  return;
4087  }
4088 
4089  num = __kmp_str_to_int( buf, *next );
4090  if ( num < 0 ) { // The number of retries should be >= 0
4091  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooSmall );
4092  num = 1;
4093  } else if ( num > KMP_INT_MAX ) {
4094  msg = KMP_I18N_STR( ValueTooLarge );
4095  num = KMP_INT_MAX;
4096  }
4097  if ( msg != NULL ) {
4098  // Message is not empty. Print warning.
4099  KMP_WARNING( ParseSizeIntWarn, name, value, msg );
4100  KMP_INFORM( Using_int_Value, name, num );
4101  }
4102  if( total == 1 ) {
4103  max_retries = num;
4104  } else if( total == 2 ) {
4105  max_badness = num;
4106  }
4107  }
4108  }
4109  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( total > 0 );
4110  if( total <= 0 ) {
4111  KMP_WARNING( EnvSyntaxError, name, value );
4112  return;
4113  }
4114  __kmp_adaptive_backoff_params.max_soft_retries = max_retries;
4115  __kmp_adaptive_backoff_params.max_badness = max_badness;
4116 }

4120 __kmp_stg_print_adaptive_lock_props(kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data )
4121 {

4123  KMP_STR_BUF_PRINT_NAME_EX(name);
4124  } else {
4125  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, " %s='", name );
4126  }
4127  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, "%d,%d'\n", __kmp_adaptive_backoff_params.max_soft_retries,
4128  __kmp_adaptive_backoff_params.max_badness );
4129 } // __kmp_stg_print_adaptive_lock_props

4152 // -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4153 // KMP_PLACE_THREADS
4154 // -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4155 
4156 static void
4157 __kmp_stg_parse_place_threads( char const * name, char const * value, void * data ) {
4158  // Value example: 5Cx2Tx15O
4159  // Which means "use 5 cores with offset 15, 2 threads per core"
4160  // AC: extended to sockets level, examples of
4161  // "use 2 sockets with offset 6, 2 cores with offset 2 per socket, 2 threads per core":
4162  // 2s,6o,2c,2o,2t; 2s,6o,2c,2t,2o; 2s@6,2c@2,2t
4163  // To not break legacy code core-offset can be last;
4164  // postfix "o" or prefix @ can be offset designator.
4165  // Note: not all syntax errors are analyzed, some may be skipped.
4166 #define CHECK_DELIM(_x) (*(_x) == ',' || *(_x) == 'x')
4167  int num;
4168  int single_warning = 0;
4169  int flagS = 0, flagC = 0, flagT = 0, flagSO = 0, flagCO = 0;
4170  const char *next = value;
4171  const char *prev;
4172 
4173  SKIP_WS(next); // skip white spaces
4174  if (*next == '\0')
4175  return; // no data provided, retain default values
4176  // Get num_sockets first (or whatever specified)
4177  if (*next >= '0' && *next <= '9') {
4178  prev = next;
4179  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4180  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4181  SKIP_WS(next);
4182  if (*next == 's' || *next == 'S') { // e.g. "2s"
4183  __kmp_place_num_sockets = num;
4184  flagS = 1; // got num sockets
4185  next++;
4186  if (*next == '@') { // socket offset, e.g. "2s@4"
4187  flagSO = 1;
4188  prev = ++next; // don't allow spaces for simplicity
4189  if (!(*next >= '0' && *next <= '9')) {
4190  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4191  return;
4192  }
4193  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4194  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4195  __kmp_place_socket_offset = num;
4196  }
4197  } else if (*next == 'c' || *next == 'C') {
4198  __kmp_place_num_cores = num;
4199  flagS = flagC = 1; // sockets were not specified - use default
4200  next++;
4201  if (*next == '@') { // core offset, e.g. "2c@6"
4202  flagCO = 1;
4203  prev = ++next; // don't allow spaces for simplicity
4204  if (!(*next >= '0' && *next <= '9')) {
4205  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4206  return;
4207  }
4208  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4209  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4210  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4211  }
4212  } else if (CHECK_DELIM(next)) {
4213  __kmp_place_num_cores = num; // no letter-designator - num cores
4214  flagS = flagC = 1; // sockets were not specified - use default
4215  next++;
4216  } else if (*next == 't' || *next == 'T') {
4217  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4218  // sockets, cores were not specified - use default
4219  return; // we ignore offset value in case all cores are used
4220  } else if (*next == '\0') {
4221  __kmp_place_num_cores = num;
4222  return; // the only value provided - set num cores
4223  } else {
4224  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4225  return;
4226  }
4227  } else {
4228  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4229  return;
4230  }
4231  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagS); // num sockets should already be set here
4232  SKIP_WS(next);
4233  if (*next == '\0')
4234  return; // " n " - something like this
4235  if (CHECK_DELIM(next)) {
4236  next++; // skip delimiter
4237  SKIP_WS(next);
4238  }
4239 
4240  // Get second value (could be offset, num_cores, num_threads)
4241  if (*next >= '0' && *next <= '9') {
4242  prev = next;
4243  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4244  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4245  SKIP_WS(next);
4246  if (*next == 'c' || *next == 'C') {
4247  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagC == 0);
4248  __kmp_place_num_cores = num;
4249  flagC = 1;
4250  next++;
4251  if (*next == '@') { // core offset, e.g. "2c@6"
4252  flagCO = 1;
4253  prev = ++next; // don't allow spaces for simplicity
4254  if (!(*next >= '0' && *next <= '9')) {
4255  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4256  return;
4257  }
4258  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4259  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4260  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4261  }
4262  } else if (*next == 'o' || *next == 'O') { // offset specified
4263  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceDeprecated);
4264  single_warning = 1;
4265  if (flagC) { // whether num_cores already specified (sockets skipped)
4266  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(!flagCO); // either "o" or @, not both
4267  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4268  } else {
4269  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(!flagSO); // either "o" or @, not both
4270  __kmp_place_socket_offset = num;
4271  }
4272  next++;
4273  } else if (*next == 't' || *next == 'T') {
4274  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagT == 0);
4275  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4276  flagC = 1; // num_cores could be skipped ?
4277  flagT = 1;
4278  next++; // can have core-offset specified after num threads
4279  } else if (*next == '\0') {
4280  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagC); // 4x2 means 4 cores 2 threads per core
4281  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4282  return; // two values provided without letter-designator
4283  } else {
4284  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4285  return;
4286  }
4287  } else {
4288  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4289  return;
4290  }
4291  SKIP_WS(next);
4292  if (*next == '\0')
4293  return; // " Ns,Nc " - something like this
4294  if (CHECK_DELIM(next)) {
4295  next++; // skip delimiter
4296  SKIP_WS(next);
4297  }
4298 
4299  // Get third value (could be core-offset, num_cores, num_threads)
4300  if (*next >= '0' && *next <= '9') {
4301  prev = next;
4302  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4303  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4304  SKIP_WS(next);
4305  if (*next == 't' || *next == 'T') {
4306  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagT == 0);
4307  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4308  if (flagC == 0)
4309  return; // num_cores could be skipped (e.g. 2s,4o,2t)
4310  flagT = 1;
4311  next++; // can have core-offset specified later (e.g. 2s,1c,2t,3o)
4312  } else if (*next == 'c' || *next == 'C') {
4313  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagC == 0);
4314  __kmp_place_num_cores = num;
4315  flagC = 1;
4316  next++;
4317  //KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(*next != '@'); // socket offset used "o" designator
4318  } else if (*next == 'o' || *next == 'O') {
4319  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceDeprecated);
4320  single_warning = 1;
4321  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagC);
4322  //KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(!flagSO); // socket offset couldn't use @ designator
4323  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4324  next++;
4325  } else {
4326  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4327  return;
4328  }
4329  } else {
4330  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4331  return;
4332  }
4333  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagC);
4334  SKIP_WS(next);
4335  if ( *next == '\0' )
4336  return;
4337  if (CHECK_DELIM(next)) {
4338  next++; // skip delimiter
4339  SKIP_WS(next);
4340  }
4341 
4342  // Get 4-th value (could be core-offset, num_threads)
4343  if (*next >= '0' && *next <= '9') {
4344  prev = next;
4345  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4346  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4347  SKIP_WS(next);
4348  if (*next == 'o' || *next == 'O') {
4349  if (!single_warning) { // warn once
4350  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceDeprecated);
4351  }
4352  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(!flagSO); // socket offset couldn't use @ designator
4353  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4354  next++;
4355  } else if (*next == 't' || *next == 'T') {
4356  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagT == 0);
4357  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4358  flagT = 1;
4359  next++; // can have core-offset specified after num threads
4360  } else {
4361  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4362  return;
4363  }
4364  } else {
4365  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4366  return;
4367  }
4368  SKIP_WS(next);
4369  if ( *next == '\0' )
4370  return;
4371  if (CHECK_DELIM(next)) {
4372  next++; // skip delimiter
4373  SKIP_WS(next);
4374  }
4375 
4376  // Get 5-th value (could be core-offset, num_threads)
4377  if (*next >= '0' && *next <= '9') {
4378  prev = next;
4379  SKIP_DIGITS(next);
4380  num = __kmp_str_to_int(prev, *next);
4381  SKIP_WS(next);
4382  if (*next == 'o' || *next == 'O') {
4383  if (!single_warning) { // warn once
4384  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceDeprecated);
4385  }
4386  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagT);
4387  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(!flagSO); // socket offset couldn't use @ designator
4388  __kmp_place_core_offset = num;
4389  } else if (*next == 't' || *next == 'T') {
4390  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT(flagT == 0);
4391  __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core = num;
4392  } else {
4393  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4394  }
4395  } else {
4396  KMP_WARNING(AffThrPlaceInvalid, name, value);
4397  }
4398  return;
4399 #undef CHECK_DELIM
4400 }

4402 static void
4403 __kmp_stg_print_place_threads( kmp_str_buf_t * buffer, char const * name, void * data ) {
4404  if (__kmp_place_num_sockets + __kmp_place_num_cores + __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core) {
4405  int comma = 0;
4406  kmp_str_buf_t buf;
4407  __kmp_str_buf_init(&buf);
4408  if(__kmp_env_format)
4409  KMP_STR_BUF_PRINT_NAME_EX(name);
4410  else
4411  __kmp_str_buf_print(buffer, " %s='", name);

4413  __kmp_str_buf_print(&buf, "%ds", __kmp_place_num_sockets);
4414  if (__kmp_place_socket_offset)
4415  __kmp_str_buf_print(&buf, "@%d", __kmp_place_socket_offset);
4416  comma = 1;
4417  }
4418  if (__kmp_place_num_cores) {

4422  comma = 1;
4423  }
4424  if (__kmp_place_num_threads_per_core)
4425  __kmp_str_buf_print(&buf, "%s%dt", comma?",":"", __kmp_place_num_threads_per_core);
4426  __kmp_str_buf_print(buffer, "%s'\n", buf.str );
4427  __kmp_str_buf_free(&buf);
4428 /*
4429  } else {
4430  __kmp_str_buf_print( buffer, " %s: %s \n", name, KMP_I18N_STR( NotDefined ) );
4431 */
4432  }

4665 static int const __kmp_stg_count = sizeof( __kmp_stg_table ) / sizeof( kmp_setting_t );
4666 
4667 static inline
4668 kmp_setting_t *
4669 __kmp_stg_find( char const * name ) {
4670 
4671  int i;
4672  if ( name != NULL ) {
4673  for ( i = 0; i < __kmp_stg_count; ++ i ) {
4674  if ( strcmp( __kmp_stg_table[ i ].name, name ) == 0 ) {
4675  return & __kmp_stg_table[ i ];
4676  }; // if
4677  }; // for
4678  }; // if
4679  return NULL;
4680 
4681 } // __kmp_stg_find

4684 static int
4685 __kmp_stg_cmp( void const * _a, void const * _b ) {
4686  kmp_setting_t * a = (kmp_setting_t *) _a;
4687  kmp_setting_t * b = (kmp_setting_t *) _b;
4688 
4689  //
4690  // Process KMP_AFFINITY last.
4691  // It needs to come after OMP_PLACES and GOMP_CPU_AFFINITY.
4692  //
4693  if ( strcmp( a->name, "KMP_AFFINITY" ) == 0 ) {
4694  if ( strcmp( b->name, "KMP_AFFINITY" ) == 0 ) {
4695  return 0;
4696  }
4697  return 1;
4698  }
4699  else if ( strcmp( b->name, "KMP_AFFINITY" ) == 0 ) {
4700  return -1;
4701  }
4702  return strcmp( a->name, b->name );
4703 } // __kmp_stg_cmp

4706 static void
4707 __kmp_stg_init( void
4708 ) {
4709 
4710  static int initialized = 0;
4711 
4712  if ( ! initialized ) {
4713 
4714  // Sort table.
4715  qsort( __kmp_stg_table, __kmp_stg_count - 1, sizeof( kmp_setting_t ), __kmp_stg_cmp );
4716 
4717  { // Initialize *_STACKSIZE data.
4718 
4719  kmp_setting_t * kmp_stacksize = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_STACKSIZE" ); // 1st priority.
4720 #ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4721  kmp_setting_t * gomp_stacksize = __kmp_stg_find( "GOMP_STACKSIZE" ); // 2nd priority.
4722 #endif
4723  kmp_setting_t * omp_stacksize = __kmp_stg_find( "OMP_STACKSIZE" ); // 3rd priority.
4724 
4725  // !!! volatile keyword is Intel (R) C Compiler bug CQ49908 workaround.
4726  // !!! Compiler does not understand rivals is used and optimizes out assignments
4727  // !!! rivals[ i ++ ] = ...;
4728  static kmp_setting_t * volatile rivals[ 4 ];
4729  static kmp_stg_ss_data_t kmp_data = { 1, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4730 #ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4731  static kmp_stg_ss_data_t gomp_data = { 1024, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4732 #endif
4733  static kmp_stg_ss_data_t omp_data = { 1024, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4734  int i = 0;
4735 
4736  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_stacksize;
4737 #ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4738  if ( gomp_stacksize != NULL ) {
4739  rivals[ i ++ ] = gomp_stacksize;
4740  }; // if
4741 #endif
4742  rivals[ i ++ ] = omp_stacksize;
4743  rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4744 
4745  kmp_stacksize->data = & kmp_data;
4746 #ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4747  if ( gomp_stacksize != NULL ) {
4748  gomp_stacksize->data = & gomp_data;
4749  }; // if
4750 #endif
4751  omp_stacksize->data = & omp_data;
4752 
4753  }
4754 
4755  { // Initialize KMP_LIBRARY and OMP_WAIT_POLICY data.
4756 
4757  kmp_setting_t * kmp_library = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_LIBRARY" ); // 1st priority.
4758  kmp_setting_t * omp_wait_policy = __kmp_stg_find( "OMP_WAIT_POLICY" ); // 2nd priority.
4759 
4760  // !!! volatile keyword is Intel (R) C Compiler bug CQ49908 workaround.
4761  static kmp_setting_t * volatile rivals[ 3 ];
4762  static kmp_stg_wp_data_t kmp_data = { 0, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4763  static kmp_stg_wp_data_t omp_data = { 1, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4764  int i = 0;
4765 
4766  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_library;
4767  if ( omp_wait_policy != NULL ) {
4768  rivals[ i ++ ] = omp_wait_policy;
4769  }; // if
4770  rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4771 
4772  kmp_library->data = & kmp_data;
4773  if ( omp_wait_policy != NULL ) {
4774  omp_wait_policy->data = & omp_data;
4775  }; // if
4776 
4777  }
4778 
4779  { // Initialize KMP_ALL_THREADS, KMP_MAX_THREADS, and OMP_THREAD_LIMIT data.
4780 
4781  kmp_setting_t * kmp_all_threads = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_ALL_THREADS" ); // 1st priority.
4782  kmp_setting_t * kmp_max_threads = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_MAX_THREADS" ); // 2nd priority.
4783  kmp_setting_t * omp_thread_limit = __kmp_stg_find( "OMP_THREAD_LIMIT" ); // 3rd priority.
4784 
4785  // !!! volatile keyword is Intel (R) C Compiler bug CQ49908 workaround.
4786  static kmp_setting_t * volatile rivals[ 4 ];
4787  int i = 0;
4788 
4789  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_all_threads;
4790  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_max_threads;
4791  if ( omp_thread_limit != NULL ) {
4792  rivals[ i ++ ] = omp_thread_limit;
4793  }; // if
4794  rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4795 
4796  kmp_all_threads->data = (void*)& rivals;
4797  kmp_max_threads->data = (void*)& rivals;
4798  if ( omp_thread_limit != NULL ) {
4799  omp_thread_limit->data = (void*)& rivals;
4800  }; // if
4801 
4802  }
4803 
4804 #if KMP_AFFINITY_SUPPORTED
4805  { // Initialize KMP_AFFINITY, GOMP_CPU_AFFINITY, and OMP_PROC_BIND data.
4806 
4807  kmp_setting_t * kmp_affinity = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_AFFINITY" ); // 1st priority.
4808  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( kmp_affinity != NULL );
4809 
4810 # ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4811  kmp_setting_t * gomp_cpu_affinity = __kmp_stg_find( "GOMP_CPU_AFFINITY" ); // 2nd priority.
4812  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( gomp_cpu_affinity != NULL );
4813 # endif
4814 
4815  kmp_setting_t * omp_proc_bind = __kmp_stg_find( "OMP_PROC_BIND" ); // 3rd priority.
4816  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( omp_proc_bind != NULL );
4817 
4818  // !!! volatile keyword is Intel (R) C Compiler bug CQ49908 workaround.
4819  static kmp_setting_t * volatile rivals[ 4 ];
4820  int i = 0;
4821 
4822  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_affinity;
4823 
4824 # ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4825  rivals[ i ++ ] = gomp_cpu_affinity;
4826  gomp_cpu_affinity->data = (void*)& rivals;
4827 # endif
4828 
4829  rivals[ i ++ ] = omp_proc_bind;
4830  omp_proc_bind->data = (void*)& rivals;
4831  rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4832 
4833 # if OMP_40_ENABLED
4834  static kmp_setting_t * volatile places_rivals[ 4 ];
4835  i = 0;
4836 
4837  kmp_setting_t * omp_places = __kmp_stg_find( "OMP_PLACES" ); // 3rd priority.
4838  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( omp_places != NULL );
4839 
4840  places_rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_affinity;
4841 # ifdef KMP_GOMP_COMPAT
4842  places_rivals[ i ++ ] = gomp_cpu_affinity;
4843 # endif
4844  places_rivals[ i ++ ] = omp_places;
4845  omp_places->data = (void*)& places_rivals;
4846  places_rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4847 # endif
4848  }
4849 #else
4850  // KMP_AFFINITY not supported, so OMP_PROC_BIND has no rivals.
4851  // OMP_PLACES not supported yet.
4852 #endif // KMP_AFFINITY_SUPPORTED
4853 
4854  { // Initialize KMP_DETERMINISTIC_REDUCTION and KMP_FORCE_REDUCTION data.
4855 
4856  kmp_setting_t * kmp_force_red = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_FORCE_REDUCTION" ); // 1st priority.
4857  kmp_setting_t * kmp_determ_red = __kmp_stg_find( "KMP_DETERMINISTIC_REDUCTION" ); // 2nd priority.
4858 
4859  // !!! volatile keyword is Intel (R) C Compiler bug CQ49908 workaround.
4860  static kmp_setting_t * volatile rivals[ 3 ];
4861  static kmp_stg_fr_data_t force_data = { 1, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4862  static kmp_stg_fr_data_t determ_data = { 0, (kmp_setting_t **)rivals };
4863  int i = 0;
4864 
4865  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_force_red;
4866  if ( kmp_determ_red != NULL ) {
4867  rivals[ i ++ ] = kmp_determ_red;
4868  }; // if
4869  rivals[ i ++ ] = NULL;
4870 
4871  kmp_force_red->data = & force_data;
4872  if ( kmp_determ_red != NULL ) {
4873  kmp_determ_red->data = & determ_data;
4874  }; // if
4875  }
4876 
4877  initialized = 1;
4878 
4879  }; // if
4880 
4881  // Reset flags.
4882  int i;
4883  for ( i = 0; i < __kmp_stg_count; ++ i ) {
4884  __kmp_stg_table[ i ].set = 0;
4885  }; // for
4886 
4887 } // __kmp_stg_init

4890 static void
4891 __kmp_stg_parse(
4892  char const * name,
4893  char const * value
4894 ) {
4895 
4896  // On Windows* OS there are some nameless variables like "C:=C:\" (yeah, really nameless, they are
4897  // presented in environment block as "=C:=C\\\x00=D:=D:\\\x00...", so let us skip them.
4898  if ( name[ 0 ] == 0 ) {
4899  return;
4900  }; // if
4901 
4902  if ( value != NULL ) {
4903  kmp_setting_t * setting = __kmp_stg_find( name );
4904  if ( setting != NULL ) {
4905  setting->parse( name, value, setting->data );
4906  setting->defined = 1;
4907  }; // if
4908  }; // if
4909 
4910 } // __kmp_stg_parse

4912 
4913 static int
4914 __kmp_stg_check_rivals( // 0 -- Ok, 1 -- errors found.
4915  char const * name, // Name of variable.
4916  char const * value, // Value of the variable.
4917  kmp_setting_t * * rivals // List of rival settings (the list must include current one).
4918 ) {
4919 
4920  if ( rivals == NULL ) {
4921  return 0;
4922  }
4923 
4924  // Loop thru higher priority settings (listed before current).
4925  int i = 0;
4926  for ( ; strcmp( rivals[ i ]->name, name ) != 0; i++ ) {
4927  KMP_DEBUG_ASSERT( rivals[ i ] != NULL );
4928 
4929 #if KMP_AFFINITY_SUPPORTED
4930  if ( rivals[ i ] == __kmp_affinity_notype ) {
4931  //
4932  // If KMP_AFFINITY is specified without a type name,
4933  // it does not rival OMP_PROC_BIND or GOMP_CPU_AFFINITY.
4934  //
4935  continue;
4936  }
4937 #endif
4938 
4939  if ( rivals[ i ]->set ) {
4940  KMP_WARNING( StgIgnored, name, rivals[ i ]->name );
4941  return 1;
4942  }; // if
4943  }; // while
4944 
4945  ++ i; // Skip current setting.
4946  return 0;
4947 
4948 }; // __kmp_stg_check_rivals
